                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">632.6231/68: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-08T19:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 8, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 8—5:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. My 147, June 6, 8 p.m., numbered paragraph 2. Exchange of notes<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d237fn17">This agreement of June 8, 1936, between Brazil and Germany
                        replaced the agreement of October 22, 1931; for text of the 1936 notes, see
                        telegram No. 152, June 10, 1 p.m., from the Ambassador in Brazil, <ref
                            target="#pg_269">p. 269</ref>.</note> was effected today prolonging
                    most-favored-nation treatment between Brazil and Germany pending conclusion of a
                    commercial treaty.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
